Description: Chambered Alder Bound Body -Tele Style Guitar with powerful pickups and a wide tonal range. Weighs 6.7 lbs. Bought this a few years back from a custom builder in New York (Peter Gebhardt). It has very little play time, Frets look new! It is finished in Nitrocellulose Lacquer, so they are a few nicks around the body, none on neck. I tried to get them in the pics. Just standard nitro stuff. Nothing dented or cracked. Tight neck pocket with no cracks! No issues other than stated nicks! Now for the good stuff! *It is a Chambered Alder body with binding. Finished in Crimson- Burst Nitro.*WD Maple neck with nice figuring.21 Nickel/Silver Medium Jumbo frets that have been leveled, crowned and polished!*vintage deluxe style Wilkinson tuners*Tusq nut, 12" radius fretboard*3 way Oak switch, Electrosocket output jack, NOS Centralab .05mf Ceramic tone cap. 250k CTS pots, Treble bleed circuit. *Fender Lace Red in the neck position. Duncan '59 in the bridge with a mini toggle switch for series/split/parallel switching!*6 Barrel Saddle Tele Style bridge*Fully copper shielded control and pickup cavities, Star grounded, Super quiet!*Vintage style cloth wire and silver solder.Will be shipped in a gigbag. Strong Blues/Rock tones from the neck position. And Tele Twang to thick hard rock from the Duncan in the bridge with the series/split/parallel mini toggle switch! Set up with 9-42's. WILL SHIP TO LOWER 48 ONLY!
Title: Custom Built Chambered Alder lightweight Telecaster (Tele) Style Guitar
